# Whitelist: the repo tracks the tool, its README, the sample config, and the
# test suite. Everything else (real config, diagnostic probes, capture script,
# status captures, generated reports, notes, __pycache__) stays local-only.
*
!README.md
!balance.py
!balance.config.json.sample

# Test suite + CI (re-include the directories, then their contents).
!.gitignore
!/tests/
!/tests/**
!/.github/
!/.github/**

# ...but never track Python bytecode or local editor caches under them.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
